Que:- What is C#?
Answer - 
â€¢ C# (Pronounced "C-Sharp") is type-safe, object-oriented programming language developed by Microsoft that runs on the .NET Framework.
â€¢ Anders Hejlsberg is the developer of the C# language.
â€¢ C# is a case-sensitive language.
â€¢ C# adopts almost all the features of C, C++, and Java programming languages, but it also includes some advanced features that are available only in C#.
â€¢ The file extension for a C# file is .cs
â€¢ C# is based on the concept of â€œobjectsâ€ which have properties (data) and methods (functions).
â€¢ Feature of C# is : Encapsulation,Inheritance,Polymorphism,Abstractions.
â€¢ C# is widely used for building:Mobile Applications,Desktop Applications,Web Services,Websites,Games,Database Applications 
â€¢ C# was created for software development in the .NET Framework.
â€¢ C# runs on the .NET platform, which provides a runtime environment called the Common Language Runtime (CLR) to execute the code.


