Que:- What is used for Input and Output in C#?
Answer:
â— Input:-Console.ReadLine() 
     â†’ Used to take input from the user
     â†’ Always returns the input as a string

â— Output:-Console.WriteLine()
     â†’ Displays output on the screen
     â†’ Moves to the next line after printing
         - Console.Write()
     â†’ Displays output but stays on the same line

Example:
   Console.WriteLine("Enter your name:");
   string name = Console.ReadLine();
   Console.WriteLine("Hello " + name);



